Guardrails & Validation
No speculation or inference. All content must trace directly to source text.
PDO: exactly one, always from the datasheet.
PAD precedence: If PAD and PID share a project ID, ignore PID (set duplicate_flag).
Citations: every item must include page citation.
Evidence length: ≤150 words, do not cut off sentences mid-way.
Species tagging: only when explicitly mentioned.
Deduplication: merge identical interventions/outcomes across sections.
Review flexibility: If extraction confidence <90%, flag but still include evidence (avoid omission).
Delivery
One Markdown report per project document.
One CSV or DOCX per IFI.
Order items as they appear in the source document.
